message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Lithuania in the past 20 years is its accession to the European Union (EU) on May 1, 2004. This event marked Lithuania's integration into the political and economic structures of the EU, bringing numerous benefits such as increased trade, investment, and opportunities for its citizens. It also symbolized the country's successful transition from a post-Soviet state to a fully-fledged member of the European community.
